org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip

Class SCgetHouseStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.common.GetHouseStatus
      • org.openhab.binding.velux.internal.bridge.slip.SCgetHouseStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BridgeCommunicationProtocol, SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol

    @NonNullByDefault
class SCgetHouseStatus
extends GetHouseStatus
implements BridgeCommunicationProtocol, SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol
    Protocol specific bridge communication supported by the Velux bridge: Retrieve House Status

    Common Message semantic: Communication from the bridge and storing returned information within the class itself.

    As 3rd level class it defines informations how to receive answer through the VeluxBridgeProvider as described by the interface SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol.

    Methods in addition to the mentioned interface:

    • getNtfNodeID() to retrieve the node identifier which has been changed.
    • getNtfState() to retrieve the state of the node which has been changed.
    • getNtfCurrentPosition() to retrieve the actual position of this node.
    • getNtfTarget() to retrieve the target position of this node.

    NOTE: the class does NOT define a request as it only works as receiver.

    Author:
    Guenther Schreiner - Initial contribution.
    See Also:
    BridgeCommunicationProtocol, SlipBridgeCommunicationProtocol
